HB 1155 Original 2026 Regular Session Robby Carter
Abstract: Provides for the use of nitrous oxide by a physician.
Proposed law authorizes a physician licensed by the La. State Board of Medical Examiners
(board) to use nitrous oxide as an analgesic during minor office surgeries and similar
procedures in accordance with board guidance and rules.
Proposed law requires the board to develop guidelines for the safe and effective use of
nitrous oxide by a physician.
Proposed law prohibits the board from banning the use of nitrous oxide in connection with
minor office surgeries and similar procedures.
(Adds R.S. 37:1274.2)
